               <p>On Thursday the 25th of August, I heard the cry of stop thief, I believe it was the prisoner, I cannot be positive, the gentleman who took him gave me the handkerchief. (Produced.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17820911-75-person826">
                  HENRY
                   CURTIS
               <interp inst="t17820911-75-person826" type="surname" value="CURTIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820911-75-person826" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820911-75-person826" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I observed the prisoner and two others picking pockets in <placeName id="t17820911-75-crimeloc392">Lombard-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17820911-75-crimeloc392" type="placeName" value="Lombard-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17820911-75-crimeloc392" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17820911-75-off390 t17820911-75-crimeloc392"></join>, I saw him put his hand in that gentleman's pocket, and take out the handkerchief; I catched him by the collar, and told Mr. Lewis; the lad struggled and fought amazingly: we took him to the compter.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>There were a great many people besides me, I never saw the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
